commitResults.messageBody:
Not using assertions at various code checkpoints like the creation of
the file and empty input commands to ensure that assumptions hold.

Adding assertions allows to properly manage the assumptions and provide
a feedback system if the code stops working.

Important code fragments that depend on external system are being
asserted of the presence of a particular assumption in place before
performing any operations.

Assert checks whether the assumptions made by the developer are correct
or not.

commitResults.messageTitle: perform critical code checks and improve the code quality
commitResults.messageBody:
The common behaviors across deadline and event input handlers cause code duplication.

Extracting the common behaviors into a method allows us to abstract out
the granularities of checking the input command.

Let's pull up behaviors common to the method which checks and
initializes important parameters for the tasks.

Making a method is preferrable here because there are only two types of
tasks that make use of this parameter check to avoid invalid commands.

add help command support
commitResults.messageBody:
Chatbot does not contain a help command for the user to understand how
to input commands.

Help command provides details regarding the input command format for the
user such that they do not run into trouble while using the chatbot.

Adding support for the help command by specifying the various commands
supported by the chatbot and their respective acceptable formats.
